$interpreted: Lio: Angel, is Cin alright?
Angelia: She's probably too exhausted. Let's bring her back to rest.
Hyacinthus: Where are the children?! Where have they gone?! Are they fooling around?! Why won't they behave?!
Hyacinthus: Why is nobody listening to me?! WHY???
Angelia: Steady now. Naya took them home already, have you forgotten?
Hyacinthus: You mean your sappy sister!? That won't do, it's too dangerous. I must take care of them myself.
Hyacinthus: If Nigel's not here...then I...shall protect...
Angelia: Hyacinthus! Calm down, please! Tell me, what's wrong?
Hyacinthus: ...GET LOST!!!
Nigel: Cin! What's going on?!
Angelia: I, I didn't touch he...Hyacinthus suddenly charged at me, I...
Naya: Wait, her hand!
Nigel: This wound... what happened?!
Naya: Could it be from Garbage Mountain, when she was shielding the children...
Nigel: Are you saying Hyacinthus was bitten by monsters?!
Nigel: Impossible! You must be mistaken!
Angelia: What? Can someone give me a rundown of what's happened?!

Nigel: Nothing. Cin will be fine, it's merely a flesh wound.
Let's go home, and I'll fetch you some medicine.
Nigel: We'll find a doctor and you'll recover in no time. Just hold on, we're going home!
Nigel: Cin, don't you give up on me now!
Angelia: What's happening? Why is Nigel acting strange?
Naya: Uh, Hyacinthus is...infected by the monsters...she might not have long to live...
Angelia: WHAT?!
